Program: Omnibus
Title: Codename Sonya
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376mkb
Last Broadcast Date: 02 January 2003
"Sonya", aka Ruth Werner and Ursula Kuczynski, was a spy who worked for the Soviet Union passing atomic secrets to Moscow. She died in 2000, never having been exposed. Her son, Michael Hamburger tells her story.